{
  "stem": "13213.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I remember looking at a map and reading about Yellow Knife in Ontario, in Ontario where there were gold mines.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But otherwise, I had never heard about Canada except that there were some aircraft manufacturers that were made in Montreal by Canadair.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, Norman Lachance convinced me to apply to the Canadian embassy.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I went, and I applied.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And within a matter of-- I don't know, must have been two years later or so, I, I worked there in the Air Force.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I got the papers from the Canadian government to say that they have a job for me in Winnipeg as an aircraft mechanic to work for the Canadian Air Force.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Well, I decided I don't want to stay in Germany.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I never wanted to live or stay in Germany.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Was just the fact that I wanted to see my cousin to visit.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And I had to stay for three years in Germany because the requirement, in order to go for Canada, you had to be a domicile, or live in a country for three years.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Otherwise, they wouldn't let you in.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I figure, I have a job, and I was a earning fairly well in the American Air Force.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I stayed there three years.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "When three years were up, the Canadian government issued a visa in Frankfurt.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in September 1955 I left Bremenhaven to Halifax, arrived on the 27th of September to Halifax.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And from Halifax, I went to on the train to Montreal.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "While I was on the boat, I was told that Winnipeg was very cold and a small city and there's not much of aircraft industries.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I decided get off in Montreal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I had saved some money.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
